main event: On June 3, 1966, a civilian observed an unidentified object over Colorado Springs, Colorado, for approximately 10 minutes.
interesting points: The observer was originally looking at the Moon when they noted the object in the sky., The object was moving at a speed comparable to that of the ECHO satellite., The report suggests that the object could have been a satellite due to the lack of any conclusive evidence., The conclusion of the visibility and presence of the object was stated as 'Satellite (Vela)'., No physical evidence or photographs were recorded in conjunction with this event.
